<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The last one’s a joke, but you get the idea – Marketcapof is perfect for anyone new or experienced in crypto and can be used to compare your favorite cryptocurrencies. </span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">2. CoinStats</span></h3>
<div id="attachment_201661" style="width: 522px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201661" class="wp-image-201661 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/oavb25520262.jpg" alt="2. CoinStats" width="512" height="284" /><p id="caption-attachment-201661" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Conistats</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">CoinStats is less of a &#8220;single calculator&#8221; and more of a complete crypto tracking ecosystem. Still, its built-in calculators and analytics tools make it one of the strongest options available in 2026.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Especially if your portfolio is spread across multiple exchanges and wallets, which, let&#8217;s be honest, describes most crypto users nowadays.</span></p>
<h4><b>Why Do People Use CoinStats</b></h4>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Automation. Instead of manually entering trades into spreadsheets like it&#8217;s 2017, CoinStats syncs directly with exchanges, wallets, and DeFi protocols.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Then it calculates:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portfolio performance;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Profit/loss;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Allocation percentages;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transaction history;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tax estimates;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Staking rewards.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">All in one place, and yes, seeing your portfolio performance in real time can be emotionally dangerous during market volatility. But at least the numbers are accurate.</span></p>
<h4><b>Key Features of CoinStats </b></h4>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Portfolio syncing;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Multi-chain support;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tax reporting tools;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Live price tracking;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">DeFi analytics;</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Mobile-friendly interface.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Another thing CoinStats does well: visualization. The dashboards are clean, readable, and beginner-friendly without feeling overly simplistic. A lot of crypto apps struggle with that balance, and some platforms prioritize advanced analytics, while others focus more heavily on visual simplicity. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">CoinStats lands somewhere in the middle.</span></p>
<h4><b>Who May Find CoinStats Useful </b></h4>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">CoinStats is ideal for:</span></p>
<ul>
